{
  "texts": [
    "Let us consider two solutions f 1 (t, A, w) and f 2 (t, A, w) of either the uncontrolled model (13) or of the controlled one (27), and assume that K[f 1](t, w) = K[f 2](t, w) for a.e.",
    "w ∈ I and any t > 0.",
    "For any initial conditions f in 1, f in 2 ∈ L 1 (R × I), if f in 1 (A, w) = f in 2 (A, w) for a.e.",
    "A ∈ R and w ∈ I, then f 1 (t, A, w) = f 2 (t, A, w) for a.e.",
    "A ∈ R, w ∈ I, and for any t > 0.Proof."
  ]
}